sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K390062
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GFP with art+ secretion tag for Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Cycle 3 mutant GFP with artifically designed secretion tag (Sergeyenko TV and Los DA. 2003. Cyanobacterial leader peptides for protein secretion. FEMS Microbiology Letters 218: 351-357) for use in Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803.
This should be a highly secreted construct (verification pending).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cody Tramp

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K390004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: art+ secretion tag for Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
In ''Synechocystis'' sp. PCC 6803, the system of secretion is based on the charge of the N-terminus leader sequence. Positive charges on the N-terminus leader sequence contribute to secretion in a non-sequence-dependent manner (Sergeyenko TV and Los DA. 2003. Cyanobacterial leader peptides for protein secretion. FEMS Microbiology Letters 218: 351-357).
This part is an artificially designed secretion tag from the above paper. It is composed of positively charged amino acids, and was shown to successfully function as a secretion tag in ''Synechocystis'' in the above paper.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cody Tramp
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is based on a sequence that was artificially designed in Sergeyenko and Los, 2003. It was created by annealing two oligionucleotides together.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
